  "prompt": "Can we change marks of autonomous marksheet?",
  "response": "Changing the marks on an autonomous marksheet can refer to two main scenarios:\n\n1. **Correcting Errors or Re-evaluations:**\n   \n   If you believe there has been an error in the calculation or recording of your marks, or if you want to request a re-evaluation of your exam papers, you can follow these legitimate procedures:\n\n   - **Contact the Examination Authority:** Reach out to the examination department of your autonomous institution. They typically have a formal process for addressing such concerns.\n   \n   - **Submit a Formal Request:** You may need to submit a written application detailing the discrepancies you\u2019ve identified, along with any supporting evidence.\n   \n   - **Re-evaluation Fees:** Be prepared to pay any applicable fees associated with re-evaluating your papers or correcting your marksheet.\n   \n   - **Follow Up:** After submitting your request, regularly follow up with the institution to check the status of your application.\n\n   **Important Tips:**\n   \n   - **Act Promptly:** There are usually deadlines for submitting requests related to marksheet corrections or re-evaluations.\n   \n   - **Maintain Professionalism:** Ensure all communications are clear, respectful, and provide all necessary documentation to support your case.\n\n2. **Illegally Altering Marks:**\n   \n   If you are referring to unlawfully changing the marks on your marksheet, it is important to understand that this is unethical and constitutes academic fraud. Engaging in such activities can have severe consequences, including:\n\n   - **Academic Penalties:** This may include suspension or expulsion from the institution.\n   \n   - **Legal Repercussions:** Altering official academic documents is a legal offense and can lead to criminal charges.\n   \n   - **Damage to Reputation:** Being involved in fraudulent activities can tarnish your personal and professional reputation, affecting future educational and career opportunities.\n\n   **Recommendation:**\n   \n   Instead of attempting to alter marks illicitly, focus on legitimate avenues to address any academic concerns you may have. If you\u2019re facing challenges with your studies, consider seeking support from academic advisors, tutors, or counselors who can provide assistance.\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nChanging marks on an autonomous marksheet is permissible only through the official and ethical channels provided by your educational institution, typically to correct genuine errors or after a formal re-evaluation process. Any attempt to alter marks dishonestly is illegal and highly discouraged.\n\nIf you need assistance with a specific issue related to your marksheet, please provide more details, and I can offer more targeted guidance.",
